  <section id="design">
    <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
    <p>Canva is a browser-based SaaS platform available on web, iOS, Android, Windows, and macOS. The core editor operates in any modern browser without installation. The 2026 addition of the free Affinity suite (Affinity Photo, Designer, Publisher) adds professional-grade vector, photo, and publishing tools alongside the browser editor, bridging the gap between Canva and Adobe Creative Cloud.</p>

    <h3>Technology Architecture</h3>
    <p>Canva's AI architecture uses a proprietary orchestration layer called "Canva Shield" and "Kaleidoscope." When a user prompts Magic Studio, the system: (1) classifies intent — determines if the request needs text, image, or layout changes; (2) injects context — brand kits and design history inform the output; (3) routes the request to the best-fit model among OpenAI's GPT-5, Google's Gemini Ultra, Runway's Gen-3, Stable Diffusion XL, Leonardo.AI's Phoenix model, and Canva's own fine-tuned models; (4) applies the safety layer — Canva Shield scans inputs and outputs for copyright infringement and safety violations before returning results to the user.</p>

    <h3>Internal Model Pipeline</h3>
    <p>This model-routing architecture means Canva can swap underlying AI providers without changing the user interface. When a user generates an image through Dream Lab, they may be using Leonardo.AI's Phoenix model; when they write copy with Magic Write, they are using an LLM; when they edit a photo with Magic Edit, the system may route to a different specialised model — all without the user needing to know or care which backend is processing their request.</p>

    <h3>Security &amp; Compliance</h3>
    <p>Canva is SOC 2 compliant and GDPR-compliant. Enterprise plans offer SSO/SAML, advanced admin controls, and dedicated security reviews. Canva Shield provides AI safety scanning for copyright and content policy violations. The platform stores user designs, brand kits, and uploaded assets in encrypted cloud storage.</p>

    <h3>Visual Appeal &amp; Trust Signals</h3>
    <p>Canva's interface is intentionally minimalist — a clean left-side panel with tools and a central canvas. The Magic Studio features are surfaced through a "Magic" button in the editor and context-sensitive suggestions. Trust signals on the public site include prominent customer logos (Expedia Group, Airbnb, Salesforce, Aramark, Kellanova), a user count of 230M+, and the Affinity acquisition as a signal of commitment to the professional market.</p>
  </section>

