    <h3>Key AI Features</h3>

    <h4>Dream Lab (AI Image Generation)</h4>
    <p>Canva's flagship AI image generator, powered by Leonardo.AI's Phoenix model as of 2026. Generates images from text prompts in multiple styles: photo, illustration, 3D rendering, painting, and more. Style Transfer support enables uploading a reference image to generate matching aesthetics. Images integrate directly into the design canvas, eliminating the download-upload-reformat workflow of standalone AI image tools. Dream Lab also supports AI video generation up to 60 seconds at 4K resolution.</p>

    <h4>Magic Write (AI Copywriting)</h4>
    <p>In-canvas AI text generator for social media captions, document drafts, marketing copy, presentation text, and more. Context-aware — it reads the design's purpose, brand voice settings, and existing content to produce relevant copy rather than generic text. The Free plan includes approximately 50 uses per month; Pro provides unlimited usage within the 500-credit pool.</p>

    <h4>Magic Design (AI Layout Generation)</h4>
    <p>Generates complete design templates from a single text prompt. Describe what you need — "Instagram story for a summer sale" — and Magic Design produces multiple layout variations with brand-compliant colours and fonts. This is one of Canva AI's strongest time-saving features: it collapses the template-browsing-and-customisation workflow into a single prompt.</p>

    <h4>Magic Edit &amp; Magic Eraser</h4>
    <p>Magic Edit replaces specific objects in photos using natural language — brush over an area and describe what you want instead. Magic Eraser removes unwanted objects, people, text, or blemishes with a single brush stroke, filling the removed area with contextually appropriate content. Both tools work on complex backgrounds including patterns, textures, and natural scenery.</p>

    <h4>Magic Expand</h4>
    <p>Extends image borders beyond their original dimensions using AI in-painting. The AI generates plausible content for expanded areas based on the existing image context. Particularly useful for reformatting images to different aspect ratios (e.g., square Instagram post to 16:9 YouTube thumbnail) without cropping important content.</p>

    <h4>Magic Grab &amp; Magic Layers</h4>
    <p>Magic Grab selects and moves subjects from flattened images. Magic Layers separates image elements into individual layers for independent editing. Together, these bridge the gap between simple template editing and professional compositing — allowing users to edit elements that would otherwise require Photoshop-level skills.</p>

    <h4>Magic Morph</h4>
    <p>Applies textures, 3D effects, and material properties to text and shapes via text prompts. Example: "make this heading look like neon glass" or "apply brushed metal texture." This adds a creative dimension to typography that would otherwise require specialised 3D design software.</p>

    <h4>Magic Switch</h4>
    <p>Transforms designs between formats with automatic reformatting — a presentation becomes a blog post, a social post becomes a flyer. Also translates designs into 150+ languages while retaining typography, layout, and brand formatting. For multilingual content creators, this is one of the most valuable and underappreciated features in Magic Studio.</p>

    <h4>Brand Kit &amp; Brand Voice AI</h4>
    <p>Brand Kit stores logos, colour palettes, fonts, and tone-of-voice guidelines. Brand Voice AI enforces these across all AI-generated copy. Free: 1 brand kit (3 colours only). Pro: 5 brand kits. Business: 100 brand kits with approval workflows. When Magic Write generates copy or Magic Design creates layouts, the AI automatically matches the brand's visual and verbal identity — saving the manual "fix the colours to match the brand" step.</p>

    <h4>Bulk Create</h4>
    <p>Generates hundreds of content variations from a single template. Replace text, images, and data across multiple designs simultaneously. For social media managers producing 20-30 graphics per week, this transforms repetitive work into a single setup-and-execute task.</p>

    <h4>Magic Charts &amp; Canva Sheets</h4>
    <p>Magic Charts generates data visualisations from spreadsheet data entered through Canva Sheets. Users pipe data into Sheets, select a chart type, and receive publication-ready infographics, bar charts, line graphs, and more. AI handles layout, labelling, and colour-coding automatically.</p>

    <h3>Areas Requiring Hands-On Validation</h3>
    <p>Several important performance characteristics cannot be assessed from documentation alone. These include: Dream Lab image quality compared to Midjourney for blog thumbnails and social graphics, Magic Write copy quality for first drafts versus heavy editing required, Bulk Create uniqueness across 100+ variations, Magic Edit accuracy on complex object replacements, Magic Expand output quality without obvious artifacts, the real-world speed at which a typical content creator exhausts 500 Pro credits, Brand Voice AI fidelity across different content types, and the point at which a power user outgrows Canva AI and needs dedicated tools. These are noted as open questions from the research.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="ux">
    <h2>User Experience</h2>
    <h3>Setup Process</h3>
    <p>Canva is accessed through a web browser at canva.com. Sign-up requires an email address or Google/Apple/Facebook account. No credit card is needed for the Free plan. AI features are surfaced through the editor interface — a "Magic" button in the side panel, context-sensitive suggestions when adding text or images, and tool-specific entry points. There is no separate AI setup process; Magic Studio is part of the editor.</p>

    <h3>Daily Usage</h3>
    <p>Ongoing activity centers on creating designs through the template library or from scratch, invoking AI tools as needed. A typical content creator workflow might be: open a new design → describe it to Magic Design → adjust with Magic Edit → write captions with Magic Write → export or schedule. The Free plan's 200 AI uses per month supports occasional use; daily content producers will need Pro.</p>

    <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
    <p>Canva's core editor is widely regarded as the most accessible design tool available — zero learning curve for basic tasks. Magic Studio follows the same philosophy: AI tools are invoked through familiar buttons and prompts rather than complex parameter menus. The AI Gear Base review notes a "steep learning curve for beginners" specifically for the AI features, but independent reviewers generally agree the interface is approachable. For anyone who has used Canva before, Magic Studio adds minimal additional complexity.</p>

    <h3>Interface &amp; Usability</h3>
    <p>We did not get hands-on access to the Magic Studio dashboard, so interface usability for the AI-specific tools is assessed from documentation and third-party descriptions. The public website presents the editor as a clean two-panel layout with tools on the left and canvas on the right. AI features are consistently described as well-integrated — invoked through buttons within the editor rather than requiring mode switches or separate screens. Magic Design creates multiple variations for the user to choose from rather than committing to a single output, which is a user-friendly design pattern.</p>
  </section>

