  <section id="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <FaqItem question="Is Canva AI free?" answer="Yes and no. Canva's Free plan includes access to some AI features (Magic Write, Dream Lab, Magic Design) but with limited usage — approximately 200 Standard AI uses or 20 Premium AI uses per month. Most of the advanced AI tools (Magic Eraser, Magic Expand, Magic Edit, Background Remover, Bulk Create) require Canva Pro ($15/month)." />
    <FaqItem question="What is Canva Magic Studio?" answer="Magic Studio is Canva's umbrella name for its AI tool suite — 25+ AI-powered features including Dream Lab (AI image generation), Magic Write (AI copywriting), Magic Edit (AI photo editing), Magic Design (AI layout generation), Magic Eraser (object removal), Magic Expand (image extension), Magic Morph (text effects), Magic Switch (format conversion + translation), Magic Charts (data visualisation), and more." />
    <FaqItem question="How much does Canva Pro cost?" answer="Canva Pro costs $15 per month when billed monthly, or $144 per year (~$12 per month) when billed annually. The annual plan saves approximately $36 compared to monthly billing. A 30-day free trial is available. Canva Business costs $20 per seat per month (or $250/year per person)." />
    <FaqItem question="How do Canva AI credits work?" answer="All premium AI features share a single monthly credit pool. On the Free plan, you get approximately 200 Standard AI uses or 20 Premium AI uses per month. On Pro, you get roughly 500 AI credits per month (about 10x the Free allowance). Different AI features consume different numbers of credits — a simple Magic Write request uses fewer credits than generating a 4K AI video. An 'AI Pass' add-on is available for users who need more." />
    <FaqItem question="Can Canva AI replace Midjourney or Photoshop?" answer="For most content creators, yes — Canva AI covers 80-90% of common design tasks. But it does not replace either tool at the expert level: Midjourney generates higher-quality, more artistic images with finer control, and Photoshop provides professional-grade editing power that Canva's simpler tools cannot match. If you need best-in-class output for a specific task, use the specialised tool. If you need good-enough output across many tasks, Canva AI is the better choice." />
    <FaqItem question="Can I use Canva AI for my team?" answer="Canva Pro is a single-user license. For team collaboration, shared brand kits, and approval workflows, you need Canva Business at $20/seat/month. Business was formerly called Canva Teams and previously had a 3-seat minimum — verify current terms at checkout." />
    <FaqItem question="Does Canva AI work in multiple languages?" answer="Yes. Canva supports 100+ languages for the interface and Magic Write can generate copy in multiple languages. Magic Switch can translate designs into 150+ languages while retaining typography, layout, and brand formatting. However, AI feature quality may vary across languages — English is typically the strongest." />
    <FaqItem question="Is Canva AI safe for commercial use?" answer="Canva is SOC 2 and GDPR compliant. The Canva Shield safety layer scans AI inputs and outputs for copyright infringement and content policy violations. However, as with any AI generation tool, users should verify that AI-generated content (text and images) does not infringe on existing copyrights or trademarks before using it commercially." />
